# Backend Environment Variables

## Local Development (SQLite)
```bash
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=development
DB_PATH=./src/database/spk_waspas.db
JWT_SECRET=your-secret-key-min-32-chars-for-production
CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000
```

## Development with Supabase
```bash
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=development
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-from-supabase
JWT_SECRET=your-secret-key-min-32-chars
CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000
```

## Production (Railway with Supabase)
```bash
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=production
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-from-supabase
JWT_SECRET=your-generated-secret-min-32-chars
CORS_ORIGIN=https://frontend-domain.railway.app
```

## Notes

- **PORT**: Default 5000, Railway reads from env
- **NODE_ENV**: Determines logging level & error details
- **SUPABASE_URL**: Your Supabase project URL (Settings > API)
- **SUPABASE_ANON_KEY**: Public anon key from Supabase (Settings > API)
- **JWT_SECRET**: Minimum 32 characters, use strong random string (openssl rand -base64 32)
- **CORS_ORIGIN**: Allow requests from frontend URL only
- **DATABASE_URL**: PostgreSQL connection string (optional, for advanced usage)

## How to Get Supabase Credentials

1. Go to https://supabase.com and create a project
2. Create a new PostgreSQL database
3. In Project Settings > API, copy:
   - Project URL → SUPABASE_URL
   - Public anon key → SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
4. Run migrations/setup using Supabase SQL Editor to create tables
